r: #ccc;"> talked yesterday</a> about the ongoing collapse of TerraUSD, or =
UST, the $18 billion algorithmic stablecoin from Terraform Labs. The basic =
idea of an algorithmic stablecoin is that you can always exchange one UST f=
or $1 worth of Luna, Terraform=E2=80=99s other cryptocurrency, which is mea=
nt to guarantee that UST always trades at $1. The risk with this sort of al=
gorithmic stablecoin is that nothing props up the price of=C2=A0<em>Luna</e=
m>, and so if people get worried about UST and try to cash out, they will g=
et $1 worth of Luna, which they will sell, which will drive down the price =
of Luna, which will make people more worried, which will lead more of them =
to cash out UST and sell Luna, which will further drive down the price of L=
una, etc., in what is known as a death spiral. Eventually cashing out $1 of=
 UST might get you, like, a trillion Luna that no one will want to buy, and=
 the whole thing might collapse.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When I wro=
te about this yesterday UST was trading at about $0.53, down about 47% from=
 where it was supposed to be,=C2=A0and Luna was trading at about $2.20, dow=
n about 93% in 24 hours. Which sounds pretty=C2=A0death-spirally.=C2=A0And =
yet it wasn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>death-spirally. Most of the h=
olders of UST had not cashed it in for Luna, in part because the smart cont=
ract that turned UST into Luna was moving too slowly to cash out all the US=
T holders who wanted out. People were just selling UST on exchanges, for pr=
ices below $1, and those UST were not being bought by arbitrageurs and tran=
sformed into $1 of Luna because the arbitrage mechanism had broken down. Do=
 Kwon, the founder of Terraform Labs and the face of UST and Luna, <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27692123.259606/aHR0cHM6L=
y90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9zdGFibGVrd29uL3N0YXR1cy8xNTI0MzMxMTgzMjYxMTYzNTIw/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB5e42eb47" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">tweeted to endorse a plan</a> to print =
Luna faster so that, you know, the death spiral could hurry up. The collaps=
e in UST and Luna prices was not purely a death spiral <em>happening</em>; =
rather, it was market prices reflecting traders=E2=80=99 <em>anticipation <=
/em>of the death spiral.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Today, though, thi=
